.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::Comment \- NIP\-22 comment threading
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::Comment;
\&
\&    # Comment on a nostr event (regular or addressable)
\&    my $comment = Net::Nostr::Comment\->comment(
\&        event     => $blog_post,
\&        pubkey    => $my_pubkey,
\&        content   => \*(AqGreat blog post!\*(Aq,
\&        relay_url => \*(Aqwss://relay.example.com\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Comment on an external identifier (URL, podcast, etc.)
\&    my $comment = Net::Nostr::Comment\->comment(
\&        identifier => \*(Aqhttps://abc.com/articles/1\*(Aq,
\&        kind       => \*(Aqweb\*(Aq,
\&        pubkey     => $my_pubkey,
\&        content    => \*(AqNice article!\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Reply to an existing comment
\&    my $reply = Net::Nostr::Comment\->reply(
\&        to        => $parent_comment,
\&        pubkey    => $my_pubkey,
\&        content   => \*(AqI agree!\*(Aq,
\&        relay_url => \*(Aqwss://relay.example.com\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Parse comment structure from an event
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Comment\->from_event($event);
\&    if ($info) {
\&        say "Root kind: " . $info\->root_kind;
\&        say "Parent kind: " . $info\->parent_kind;
\&    }
\&
\&    # Validate a comment event
\&    Net::Nostr::Comment\->validate($event);
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-22 comment threading for kind 1111 events. Comments are
plaintext threading notes scoped to a root event or external identifier.
.PP
Comments use uppercase tags (\f(CW\*(C`E\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`A\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`I\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`K\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`P\*(C'\fR) for the root
scope and lowercase tags (\f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR) for the parent
item. For top\-level comments, root and parent point to the same target.
.PP
Comments MUST NOT be used to reply to kind 1 notes; use
Net::Nostr::Thread (NIP\-10) instead.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 1
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Comment\->new(%fields);
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Comment\*(C'\fR object. Typically returned by
"from_event"; calling \f(CW\*(C`new\*(C'\fR directly is useful for testing or
manual construction.
.PP
.Vb 6
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Comment\->new(
\&        root_tag_name => \*(AqE\*(Aq,
\&        root_kind     => \*(Aq30023\*(Aq,
\&        root_value    => \*(Aqabc123\*(Aq,
\&        root_pubkey   => $hex_pubkey,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Accepted fields: \f(CW\*(C`root_tag_name\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`root_value\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`root_relay\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`root_kind\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`root_pubkey\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`parent_tag_name\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`parent_value\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`parent_relay\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`parent_kind\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`parent_pubkey\*(C'\fR.
Croaks on unknown arguments.
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS comment
.IX Subsection "comment"
.Vb 9
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Comment\->comment(
\&        event      => $target_event,       # nostr event to comment on
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,
\&        content    => \*(Aqcomment text\*(Aq,
\&        relay_url  => \*(Aqwss://relay.com/\*(Aq,  # optional, defaults to \*(Aq\*(Aq
\&        quotes     => [{id => $eid, relay_url => $r, pubkey => $pk}],  # optional
\&        mentions   => [$pubkey1],          # optional
\&        created_at => time(),              # optional, passed to Event
\&    );
\&
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Comment\->comment(
\&        identifier => \*(Aqhttps://example.com/article\*(Aq,
\&        kind       => \*(Aqweb\*(Aq,
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,
\&        content    => \*(Aqcomment text\*(Aq,
\&        hint       => \*(Aqhttps://...\*(Aq,       # optional hint for I/i tags
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 1111 comment event. Pass \f(CW\*(C`event\*(C'\fR for nostr events or
\&\f(CW\*(C`identifier\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`kind\*(C'\fR for external identifiers (URLs, podcasts, etc.).
.PP
For addressable events (kinds 30000\-39999), generates \f(CW\*(C`A\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tags with
the event coordinate and an additional \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag referencing the event ID.
For regular events, generates \f(CW\*(C`E\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tags. Tags \f(CW\*(C`K\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR are always
included with the target kind, and \f(CW\*(C`P\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tags include the author pubkey
for nostr events.
.PP
Croaks if the target is a kind 1 event (use Net::Nostr::Thread instead).
.PP
.Vb 6
\&    # Comment on a NIP\-94 file event
\&    my $comment = Net::Nostr::Comment\->comment(
\&        event   => $file_event,
\&        pubkey  => $my_pk,
\&        content => \*(AqGreat file!\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Comment on a podcast episode
\&    my $comment = Net::Nostr::Comment\->comment(
\&        identifier => \*(Aqpodcast:item:guid:d98d189b\-...\*(Aq,
\&        kind       => \*(Aqpodcast:item:guid\*(Aq,
\&        pubkey     => $my_pk,
\&        content    => \*(AqGreat episode!\*(Aq,
\&        hint       => \*(Aqhttps://fountain.fm/episode/...\*(Aq,
\&    );
.Ve
.SS reply
.IX Subsection "reply"
.Vb 8
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Comment\->reply(
\&        to         => $parent_comment,
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,
\&        content    => \*(Aqreply text\*(Aq,
\&        relay_url  => \*(Aqwss://relay.com/\*(Aq,  # optional
\&        quotes     => [...],               # optional
\&        mentions   => [...],               # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 1111 reply to an existing comment. The root scope tags
(\f(CW\*(C`E\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`A\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`I\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`K\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`P\*(C'\fR) are preserved from the parent comment\*(Aqs
uppercase tags. The parent tags point to the comment being replied to
with \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR set to \f(CW1111\fR.
.PP
.Vb 5
\&    my $reply = Net::Nostr::Comment\->reply(
\&        to      => $comment_event,
\&        pubkey  => $my_pk,
\&        content => \*(AqI agree!\*(Aq,
\&    );
.Ve
.SS from_event
.IX Subsection "from_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Comment\->from_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Parses comment structure from a kind 1111 event. Returns a
\&\f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Comment\*(C'\fR object with accessors for root and parent scope,
or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if the event is not kind 1111.
.PP
.Vb 4
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Comment\->from_event($event);
\&    say $info\->root_kind;       # \*(Aq30023\*(Aq
\&    say $info\->parent_kind;     # \*(Aq1111\*(Aq (if replying to a comment)
\&    say $info\->root_pubkey;     # root event author, or undef
.Ve
.SS validate
.IX Subsection "validate"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::Comment\->validate($event);
.Ve
.PP
Validates that an event is a well\-formed NIP\-22 comment. Croaks if:
.IP \(bu 4
Kind is not 1111
.IP \(bu 4
Missing root scope tag (\f(CW\*(C`E\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`A\*(C'\fR, or \f(CW\*(C`I\*(C'\fR)
.IP \(bu 4
Missing parent scope tag (\f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR, or \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR)
.IP \(bu 4
Missing \f(CW\*(C`K\*(C'\fR tag (root kind)
.IP \(bu 4
Missing \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag (parent kind)
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    eval { Net::Nostr::Comment\->validate($event) };
\&    warn "Invalid comment: $@" if $@;
.Ve
